The paper discusses optimization of parameterized policies for reinforcement learning, which is a common problem in machine learning. The focus is on partially-observable multiagent environments, which suggests categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The paper also discusses actor-critic algorithms, which are commonly used in reinforcement learning, suggesting categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses convergence guarantees and regret minimization, which are topics in game theory, suggesting a category such as cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
